<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<tittle>Simple Selectors</tittle>
<style> /* Element selector*/
p{
 color: blue;
}
/* ID selector */
#main{
  color: red;
}
/* Class selector */
.note{
  color: green;
}
/* Group selector */
h1, h2 {
     text - align: center;
}
/* Universal selector */
* {
   font - family: Arial;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1 id="main">CSS Selector</h1>
<h2>INTRODUCTION</h2>

<p>SELECTOR FORM.</p>
<p class="note">A CSS selector is used to select HTML elements so that we can apply style (color, size, layout, etc.) to them.</p>
</body>
</html>
